The paper deals with clustering of high-dimensional polygonal curves, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of random projections and subsampling, which are common techniques in machine learning and data mining. Hence, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also evaluates its results on real-world data from various physical domains, which suggests that it may be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and database systems (cs.DB).
